description:
Bug 38131ajc needs -d. I am using 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I am guessing this may have something to do with a change in the underlying Eclipse compiler. Create a class in a subpackage such as:

package subpackage;

public class Test {

	public static void main(String[] args) {

		System.out.println("Hello");

	}

}

Then compile using the following command: ajc subpackage\Test.java

You will see a directory "subpackage" created under the existing "subpackage" directory. subpackage\Test.java or javac subpackage\Test.java. No big deal, really.
